# Bee Kiss Premium E-Commerce Website Implementation

## Goal Description
Create a premium e-commerce website for a luxury forest honey brand "Bee Kiss" from Wayanad, Kerala. The site will feature a dark forest green and honey gold aesthetic, emotional storytelling, a fully functional frontend cart system, and responsive mobile-first design built with Vanilla HTML, CSS, and JS. This ensures maximum performance, SEO optimization, and fine-grained control over the modern fade animations.

## Proposed Changes

### Project Structure (`C:\Users\fresh\.gemini\antigravity\scratch\beekiss`)

#### [NEW] `index.html`
Main landing page containing all requested sections:
- Hero
- Our Story
- Products
- Why Bee Kiss
- Purity Education
- Reviews
- Footer (Contact, WhatsApp, Policies)
Includes SEO meta tags and semantic HTML5 elements.

#### [NEW] `checkout.html`
A dedicated checkout page displaying cart items, total calculation, and a mock "Razorpay" payment integration placeholder button.

#### [NEW] `css/styles.css`
Vanilla CSS implementation of the design system:
- Premium color palette (`#0F2E1D` dark forest green, `#D4A017` honey gold, cream white).
- Typography (Google Fonts - Playfair Display for serif headings, Inter for sans-serif body).
- Responsive grid/flex layouts for mobile-first rendering.
- Smooth CSS fade animations and hover effects for a luxury feel.

#### [NEW] `js/app.js`
Frontend logic for:
- Managing the shopping cart via `localStorage`.
- Handling product weight selection.
- Animating elements on scroll (Intersection Observer).
- Updating the cart slide-out/modal UI dynamically.

#### [NEW] `js/checkout.js`
Logic for:
- Rendering the cart on the checkout page.
- Calculating totals.
- Mocking the Razorpay checkout process.

#### [NEW] `images/` directory
AI-generated placeholder images for the hero background, founder/story section, and product packaging to provide a premium look from the start.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- None required (Frontend-only static site without backend integration).

### Manual Verification
- Start a local HTTP server and view the site in the browser to ensure the premium design aesthetic and styling exactly match the required brand positioning.
- Test responsive layout on mobile, tablet, and desktop viewports.
- Interact with the product cards: change weights, add items to the cart, and observe cart UI updates.
- Proceed to checkout via the cart and ensure the Razorpay placeholder functions correctly.
